# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
# |<----  Using a maximum of 50 characters  ---->|

# Explain why this change is being made
# |<----   Try to limit each line to 72 characters   ---->|

# Provide links to any relevant tickets, issues, or resources
# Use "Fixes #<issue>" to auto-close the issue on merge

# --- COMMIT END ---
# Type can be:
#   feat     (new feature)
#   fix      (bug fix)
#   docs     (changes to documentation)
#   style    (formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change)
#   refactor (refactoring production code)
#   test     (adding tests, refactoring tests; no production code change)
#   chore    (updating tasks, dependencies etc; no production code change)
#
# Scope can be:
#   batch     (trade_batch service)
#   dashboard (trade_dashboard service)
#   engine    (trade_engine service)
#   frontend  (trade_frontend service)
#   infra     (infrastructure)
#   common    (shared resources)
#   all       (changes affecting multiple services)
#
# Remember to:
#   - Use the imperative mood ("add" not "added")
#   - Don't end with a period
#   - Separate subject from body with a blank line
#   - Use the body to explain what and why, not how